<p><a name="Recordings" id="Recordings"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_Hindemith&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Recordings">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Recordings</span></h2>
<p>His complete orchestral works have been recorded by the German conductor <a href="/wiki/Werner_Andreas_Albert" title="Werner Andreas Albert">Werner Andreas Albert</a>.</p>
<p><a name="Hindemithon_Festival" id="Hindemithon_Festival"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_Hindemith&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Hindemithon Festival">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Hindemithon Festival</span></h2>
<p>A yearly festival of Hindemith's music, <a href="http://www.hindemithon.com" class="external text" title="http://www.hindemithon.com" rel="nofollow"><i>Hindemithon</i></a>, is held at <a href="/wiki/William_Paterson_University" title="William Paterson University">William Paterson University</a> in Wayne, New Jersey.</p>
